user_query:
I need a reproducible micro-benchmark and summary. Read input/commands.json to get two Python commands (fast and slow). Then:

1) Run `benchmark-tool run <cmd>` for each command and save the full stdout to:
- output/raw/run_fast.txt
- output/raw/run_slow.txt

2) Run `benchmark-tool compare <fast_cmd> <slow_cmd>` in that order and save the full stdout to:
- output/raw/compare.txt

3) Parse the three raw logs and create output/report.json with this exact schema and rounding:
{
  "tool": "Benchmark Tool",
  "commands": {"fast": "<fast_cmd>", "slow": "<slow_cmd>"},
  "runs_used": {"run": 10, "compare_each": 5},
  "run": {
    "fast": {"mean": <float>, "median": <float>, "min": <float>, "max": <float>, "stddev": <float>},
    "slow": {"mean": <float>, "median": <float>, "min": <float>, "max": <float>, "stddev": <float>}
  },
  "compare": {"fast_avg": <float>, "slow_avg": <float>}
}
- All numeric values must be rounded to 3 decimal places to match the tool's printed statistics.
- Extract values only from the logs (do not re-compute from timings independently).

Use only relative paths. Create any missing directories under output/.
